refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 OpenSSLAsymmetricKeyfalseopenssl_pkey_new
 arraynulloptions&null;



 openssl_pkey_new generates a new private
 key.
 How to obtain the public component of the key is shown in an example below.

&note.openssl.cnf;

&reftitle.parameters;
options
You can finetune the key generation (such as specifying the number of bits) using options. See openssl_csr_new for more information about options.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns an OpenSSLAsymmetricKey instance for the pkey on success, or &false; on
 error.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     On success, this function returns an OpenSSLAsymmetricKey instance now;
     previously, a &resource; of type OpenSSL key was returned.




    7.1.0
    The curve_name option was added to make it possible to create EC keys.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Obtain the public key from a private key


<?php
$private_key = openssl_pkey_new();
$public_key_pem = openssl_pkey_get_details($private_key)['key'];
echo $public_key_pem;
$public_key = openssl_pkey_get_public($public_key_pem);
var_dump($public_key);
?>


